  "decision_conditions": [
    "The development, by reason of its position, size, scale and materials, constitutes an intrusive, incongruous and prominent feature, out of keeping with and detrimental to the character of the area and adjacent primary shopping frontage. The development fails to comply with Policies D3 and D4 of the London Plan (2021) and Policies 4B, 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013). | The proposed development, by reason of its lack of doors or shutters, would be left open to the public when the shop is closed and would fail to sufficiently design out crime to the detriment of the safety of neighbouring residents, adjoining uses and pedestrians. The proposal would fail to comply with Policy D11 of the London Plan (2021)."
